data.event: The Town of Fremont was first settled in the spring of 1849 by D. Gordon.

event.title: published was the Fremont Pioneer in 1857

data.event: The first paper published was the Fremont Pioneer in 1857.
The first church (Presbyterian) was built in 1873.
The village of Fremont was organized in 1888.

event.title: takes place in the summer of 1852

data.event: The story of the "Death of Wau-Ke-John", a war chief of the Menominee, takes place in the summer of 1852 as reported by W. A. Springer "who was in the neighborhood ... and was present at the funeral".
A spawning run of white bass, or sand bass (Morone chrysops), also known as "stripers", occurs twice a year - in May around Mother's Day and in late September to early October.
